examples.korean: She’d been seeing the boy for a while, but didn’t want her parents to find out. 발음듣기 그녀는 그 남자애를 오랫동안 만나 왔지만 부모님이 알게 되기를 원하지 않았다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: She’d been seeing the boy for a while, but didn’t want her parents to find out. 발음

examples.korean: I’ll take any you don’t want. 발음듣기 난 네가 원하지 않는 거 아무거나 할게. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: I’ll take any you don’t want. 발음

examples.korean: His parents didn’t want him to go on the stage. 발음듣기 그의 부모는 그가 배우가 되는 것을 원하지 않았다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: His parents didn’t want him to go on the stage. 발음

examples.korean: The company wants to keep down labour costs. 발음듣기 회사에서는 작업비가 늘어나는 것을 원하지 않는다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: The company wants to keep down labour costs. 발음

examples.korean: We do not want any extraneous information on the page. 발음듣기 우리는 그 페이지에 관련 없는 정보는 어떤 것도 원하지 않는다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: We do not want any extraneous information on the page. 발음
